ss and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "1.8 Save for those provisions of CPR Part 31 that are set out in Section II, and the related provisions of Practice Directions 31 A and 31 B, CPR Part 31 and Practice Directions 31 A and 31 B shall not apply to any proceedings falling within this Practice Direction.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_7", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "1.8", "subsection_index": 7, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "1.9, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "1.9 Save that references in Section II to an Electronic Documents Questionnaire should be treated as references to the Disclosure Review Document, nothing in this Practice Direction is intended to change the application or working of those provisions of CPR Part 31 that are set out in Section II and the related provisions of Practice Directions 31 A and 31 B, and CPR Part 31 as a whole should still be used to interpret those provisions.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_8", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "1.9", "subsection_index": 8, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "1.10, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "1.10 Provisions relating to Extended Disclosure in Less Complex Claims are contained in Appendix 5. Less Complex Claims are defined in paragraph 1.9 of Appendix 1 to this Practice Direction.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_9", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "1.10", "subsection_index": 9, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "1.11, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "1.11 This Practice Direction applies in multi-party cases. However, the court may order that the timetable and procedure is to be varied so as to provide a bespoke timetable and procedure to meet the needs of the individual multi-party case. Any application to the court in this connection should be made at an early stage.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_10", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "1.11", "subsection_index": 10, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "1.12, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "1.12 A party seeking an order for disclosure in a Part 8 claim shall serve and file a List of Issues for Disclosure in relation to which disclosure is sought and the Models that are to be adopted for each issue. The court may adapt the provisions of this Practice Direction in such manner as may be appropriate when making an order for disclosure in a Part 8 claim. SECTION I 2. Principles, "document", "adverse" and "known adverse documents"", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_11", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "1.12", "subsection_index": 11, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.1 Disclosure is important in achieving the fair resolution of civil proceedings. It involves identifying and making available documents that are relevant to the issues in the proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_12", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.1", "subsection_index": 12, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.2 For the purpose of disclosure, the term "document" includes any record of any description containing information. The term is further defined below.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_13", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.2", "subsection_index": 13, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.3 The court expects the parties (and their representatives) to cooperate with each other and to assist the court so that the scope of disclosure, if any, that is required in proceedings can be agreed or determined by the court in the most efficient way possible.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_14", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.3", "subsection_index": 14, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.4 The court will be concerned to ensure that disclosure is directed to the issues in the proceedings and that the scope of disclosure is not wider than is reasonable and proportionate (as defined in paragraph 6.4) in order fairly to resolve those issues, and specifically the Issues for Disclosure (as defined in paragraph 7.6).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_15", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.4", "subsection_index": 15, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.5 A "document" may take any form including but not limited to paper or electronic; it may be held by computer or on portable devices such as memory sticks or mobile phones or within databases; it includes e-mail and other electronic communications such as text messages, webmail, social media and voicemail, audio or visual recordings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_16", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.5", "subsection_index": 16, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.6, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.6 In addition to information that is readily accessible from computer systems and other electronic devices and media, the term "document" extends to information that is stored on servers and back-up systems and electronic information that has been 'deleted'. It also extends to metadata, and other embedded data which is not typically visible on screen or a printout.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_17", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.6", "subsection_index": 17, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.7, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.7 Disclosure extends to "adverse" documents. A document is "adverse" if it or any information it contains contradicts or materially damages the disclosing party's contention or version of events on an issue in dispute, or supports the contention or version of events of an opposing party on an issue in dispute, whether or not that issue is one of the agreed Issues for Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_18", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.7", "subsection_index": 18, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.8, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.8"Known adverse documents" are documents (other than privileged documents) that a party is actually aware (without undertaking any further search for documents than it has already undertaken or caused to be undertaken) both (a) are or were previously within its control and (b) are adverse.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_19", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.8", "subsection_index": 19, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.9, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.9 For this purpose a company or organisation is "aware" if any person with accountability or responsibility within the company or organisation for the events or the circumstances which are the subject of the case, or for the conduct of the proceedings, is aware. For this purpose it is also necessary to take reasonable steps to check the position with any person who has had such accountability or responsibility but who has since left the company or organisation. 3. Duties in relation to disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_20", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.9", "subsection_index": 20, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "3.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "3.1 A person who knows that it is or may become a party to proceedings that have been commenced or who knows that it may become a party to proceedings that may be commenced is under the following duties ("the Disclosure Duties") to the court-

(1) to take reasonable steps to preserve documents in its control that may be relevant to any issue in the proceedings;

(2) by no later than the time(s) set out in paragraphs 9.1 to 9.3, to disclose known adverse documents, unless they are privileged. This duty exists regardless of whether or not any order for disclosure is made;

(3) to comply with any order for disclosure made by the court;

(4) to undertake any search for documents in a responsible and conscientious manner to fulfil the stated purpose of the search;

(5) to act honestly in relation to the process of giving disclosure and reviewing documents disclosed by the other party; and

(6) to use reasonable efforts to avoid providing documents to another party that have no relevance to the Issues for Disclosure in the proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_21", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "3.1", "subsection_index": 21, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "3.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "3.2 Legal representatives who have the conduct of litigation on behalf of a party to proceedings that have been commenced, or who are instructed with a view to the conduct of litigation where their client knows it may become a party to proceedings that have been or may be commenced, are under the following duties to the court-

(1) to take reasonable steps to preserve documents within their control that may be relevant to any issue in the proceedings;

(2) to take reasonable steps to advise and assist the party to comply with its Disclosure Duties;

(3) to liaise and cooperate with the legal representatives of the other parties to the proceedings (or the other parties where they do not have legal representatives) so as to promote the reliable, efficient and cost-effective conduct of disclosure, including through the use of technology;

(4) to act honestly in relation to the process of giving disclosure and reviewing documents disclosed by the other party; and

(5) to undertake a review to satisfy themselves that any claim by the party to privilege from disclosing a document is properly made and the reason for the claim to privilege is sufficiently explained.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_22", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "3.2", "subsection_index": 22, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "3.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "3.3 The duties under paragraphs 3.1 and 3.2 above are continuing duties that last until the conclusion of the proceedings (including any appeal) or until it is clear there will be no proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_23", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "3.3", "subsection_index": 23, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "3.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "3.4 Where there is a known adverse document but it has not been located, the duty to disclose the document is met by that fact being disclosed, subject to any further order that the court may make. 4. Preservation of documents", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_24", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "3.4", "subsection_index": 24, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.1 Documents to be preserved in accordance with the duties under paragraphs 3.1(1) and 3.2(1) above include documents which might otherwise be deleted or destroyed in accordance with a document retention policy or in the ordinary course of business. Preservation includes, in suitable cases, making copies of sources and documents and storing them.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_25", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.1", "subsection_index": 25, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.2 The duty under paragraph 3.1(1) and 3.2(1) includes-

(1) an obligation to suspend relevant document deletion or destruction processes for the duration of the proceedings;

(2) in accordance with paragraph 4.3 below, an obligation to send a written notification in any form to relevant employees and former employees of the party where there are reasonable grounds for believing that the employee or former employee may be in possession of disclosable documents which are not also in the party's possession; and

(3) an obligation to take reasonable steps so that agents or third parties who may hold documents on the party's behalf do not delete or destroy documents that may be relevant to an issue in the proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_26", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.2", "subsection_index": 26, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.3 A written notification under paragraph 4.2 above should-

(1) identify the documents or classes of documents to be preserved; and

(2) notify the recipient that they should not delete or destroy those documents and should take reasonable steps to preserve them.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_27", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.3", "subsection_index": 27, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.4 Legal representatives who have the conduct of litigation on behalf of a party to proceedings that have been commenced, or who are instructed with a view to the conduct of litigation where their client knows it may become a party to proceedings that have been or may be commenced, must within a reasonable period of being instructed-

(1) notify their client of the need to preserve documents and of their obligations under paragraph 3.1 above; and

(2) obtain written confirmation from their client or an appropriate representative of their client that their client has taken the steps required under paragraphs 4.2 and 4.3 above.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_28", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.4", "subsection_index": 28, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.5 Each party must confirm in writing (and may do so by their legal representative) when serving their particulars of claim or defence (as appropriate), that steps have been taken to preserve relevant documents in accordance with the duties under paragraph 3.1(1) and 3.2(1) above, and as required by paragraph 4.1 to 4.4 above. 5. Initial Disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_29", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.5", "subsection_index": 29, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.1 Save as provided below, and save in the case of a Part 7 claim form without particulars of claim, each party must provide to all other parties at the same time as its statement of case an Initial Disclosure List of Documents that lists and is accompanied by copies of-

(1) the key documents on which it has relied (expressly or otherwise) in support of the claims or defences advanced in its statement of case (and including the documents referred to in that statement of case); and

(2) the key documents that are necessary to enable the other parties to understand the claim or defence they have to meet.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_30", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.1", "subsection_index": 30, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.2 This form of disclosure is known as "Initial Disclosure".", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_31", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.2", "subsection_index": 31, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.3 Initial Disclosure is not required where-

(1) the parties have agreed to dispense with it (see paragraph 5.8 below);

(2) the court has ordered that it is not required (see paragraph 5.10 below); or

(3) a party concludes and states in writing, approaching the matter in good faith, that giving Initial Disclosure would involve it or any other party providing (after removing duplicates, and including documents referred to at paragraph 5.4(3)(a)) more than (about) whichever is the larger of 1000 pages or 200 documents (or such higher but reasonable figure as the parties may agree), at which point the requirement to give Initial Disclosure ceases for all parties for the purposes of the case.

Documents comprising media not in page form are not included in the calculation of the page or document limit at (3) but, where provided pursuant to a requirement to give Initial Disclosure, should be confined strictly to what is necessary to comply with paragraph 5.1 above.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_32", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.3", "subsection_index": 32, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.4 A party giving Initial Disclosure-

(1) is under no obligation to undertake a search for documents beyond any search it has already undertaken or caused to be undertaken for the purposes of the proceedings (including in advance of the commencement of the proceedings);

(2) need not provide unless requested documents by way of Initial Disclosure if such documents-

(a) have already been provided to the other party, whether by disclosure before proceedings start (see CPR 31.16) or through pre-action correspondence or otherwise in the period following intimation of the proceedings (and including when giving Initial Disclosure with a statement of case that is being amended); or

(b) are known to be or have been in the other party's possession;

(3) need not disclose adverse documents by way of Initial Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_33", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.4", "subsection_index": 33, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.5 Unless otherwise ordered, or agreed between the parties, copies of documents shall be provided in electronic form for the purpose of Initial Disclosure. The Initial Disclosure List of Documents should be filed but the documents must not be filed.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_34", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.5", "subsection_index": 34, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.6, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.6 In proceedings where a statement of case is to be served on a defendant out of the jurisdiction Initial Disclosure is not required in respect of that defendant unless and until that defendant files an acknowledgement of service that does not contest the jurisdiction, or files a further acknowledgement of service under CPR 11(7)(b).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_35", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.6", "subsection_index": 35, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.7, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.7 For the avoidance of doubt, Initial Disclosure does not require any document to be translated.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_36", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.7", "subsection_index": 36, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.8, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.8 The parties may agree in writing, before or after the commencement of proceedings, to dispense with, or defer, Initial Disclosure. They may also agree to dispense with the requirement to produce an Initial Disclosure List of Documents. Each party should record its respective reasons for any agreement, so that those reasons may be available to the court, on request, at any case management conference. The court may set aside an agreement to dispense with or defer Initial Disclosure if it considers that Initial Disclosure is likely to provide significant benefits and the costs of providing Initial Disclosure are unlikely to be disproportionate to such benefits.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_37", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.8", "subsection_index": 37, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.9, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.9 The court shall disregard any prior agreement to dispense with Initial Disclosure when considering whether to order Extended Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_38", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.9", "subsection_index": 38, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.10, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.10 A party may apply to the court for directions limiting or abrogating the obligation to provide Initial Disclosure. In particular, if a party is requested but does not agree to dispense with Initial Disclosure, the requesting party may apply to the court with notice to the other party for directions limiting or abrogating the obligation to provide Initial Disclosure if it considers compliance with the obligation will incur disproportionate cost or be unduly complex. Such an application must be made by application notice, supported by evidence where necessary, and, save in exceptional cases, will be dealt with without a hearing or at a short telephone hearing.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_39", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.10", "subsection_index": 39, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.11, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.11 In an appropriate case the court may, on application, and whether or not Initial Disclosure has been given, require a party to disclose documents to another party where that is necessary to enable the other party to understand the claim or defence they have to meet or to formulate a defence or a reply.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_40", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.11", "subsection_index": 40, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.12, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.12 A complaint about Initial Disclosure shall be dealt with at the first case management conference unless, exceptionally and on application, the court considers that the issue should be resolved at an earlier hearing.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_41", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.12", "subsection_index": 41, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.13, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.13 A significant failure to comply with the obligation to provide Initial Disclosure may be taken into account by the court when considering whether to make an order for Extended Disclosure and the terms of such an order. It may also result in an adverse order for costs.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_42", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.13", "subsection_index": 42, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.14, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.14 For the avoidance of doubt, nothing in this paragraph affects the operation of paragraph 7.3 of Practice Direction 16. 6. Extended Disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_43", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.14", "subsection_index": 43, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.1 A party wishing to seek disclosure of documents in addition to, or as an alternative to, Initial Disclosure must request Extended Disclosure. No application notice is required. However, the parties will be expected to have completed the Disclosure Review Document pursuant to paragraphs 7 and following below.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_44", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.1", "subsection_index": 44, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.2 Save where otherwise provided, Extended Disclosure involves using Disclosure Models (see paragraph 8 below) in respect of Issues for Disclosure which have been identified (see paragraph 7 below).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_45", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.2", "subsection_index": 45, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.3 The court will only make an order for Extended Disclosure that is search-based (ie Models C, D and/or E) where it is persuaded that it is appropriate to do so in order fairly to resolve one or more of the Issues for Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_46", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.3", "subsection_index": 46, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.4 In all cases, an order for Extended Disclosure must be reasonable and proportionate having regard to the overriding objective including the following factors-

(1) the nature and complexity of the issues in the proceedings;

(2) the importance of the case, including any non-monetary relief sought;

(3) the likelihood of documents existing that will have probative value in supporting or undermining a party's claim or defence;

(4) the number of documents involved;

(5) the ease and expense of searching for and retrieval of any particular document (taking into account any limitations on the information available and on the likely accuracy of any costs estimates);

(6) the financial position of each party; and

(7) the need to ensure the case is dealt with expeditiously, fairly and at a proportionate cost.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_47", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.4", "subsection_index": 47, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.5 A request for search-based Extended Disclosure (ie Models C, D and/or E) must specify which of the Disclosure Models listed in paragraph 8 below is proposed for each Issue for Disclosure defined in paragraph 7 below. It is for the party requesting Extended Disclosure to show that what is sought is appropriate, reasonable and proportionate (as defined in paragraph 6.4).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_48", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.5", "subsection_index": 48, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.6, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.6 The objective of relating Disclosure Models to Issues for Disclosure is to limit the searches required and the volume of documents to be disclosed. Issues for Disclosure may be grouped. Disclosure Models should not be used in a way that increases cost through undue complexity.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_49", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.6", "subsection_index": 49, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.7, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.7 It is important that the parties consider what types of documents and sources of documents there are or may be, including what documents another party is likely to have, in order that throughout a realistic approach may be taken to disclosure.

Court control over disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_50", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.7", "subsection_index": 50, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.8, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.8 The court will determine whether to order Extended Disclosure at the first case management conference or, if directed by the court, at another hearing convened for that purpose or without a hearing.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_51", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.8", "subsection_index": 51, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.9, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.9 The court may determine any point at issue between the parties about disclosure including the application or effect of any provision in this Practice Direction or an order made by the court and about the scope of searches, the manner in which searches are to be carried out and the use of technology. The parties may, at any time, apply to the court to seek the determination of an issue concerning disclosure by issuing an application notice.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_52", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.9", "subsection_index": 52, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.10, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.10 The court may also provide disclosure guidance in accordance with paragraph 11.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_53", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.10", "subsection_index": 53, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.11, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.11 Upon the application of the parties/a party, or on its own motion, the court may vary any period of time for a party/the parties to complete a step in disclosure. If the variation is agreed between the parties and will not affect the date set for the Case Management Conference or trial (as appropriate), court approval is not required. 7. Identifying the Issues for Disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_54", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.11", "subsection_index": 54, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.1 Within 28 days of the final statement of case each party should state, in writing, whether or not it is likely to request search-based Extended Disclosure to include one or more of Models C, D or E (see paragraph 8 below) on one or more Issues for Disclosure in the case. At this point it should not particularise the Model(s) or the issue(s) in the case.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_55", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.1", "subsection_index": 55, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.2 Where one or more of the parties has indicated it is likely to request search-based Extended Disclosure (i.e. Models C, D and/or E), the claimant must within 42 days of the final statement of case prepare and serve on the other parties a draft List of Issues for Disclosure unless an agreed list of issues for trial already exists and the parties agree that it is suitable (with or without adaptation) to be used for disclosure. The draft List of Issues for Disclosure should be set out in Section 1 A of the Disclosure Review Document.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_56", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.2", "subsection_index": 56, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.3 At the same time as serving a draft List of Issues for Disclosure, the claimant shall identify for each Issue for Disclosure which Model of Extended Disclosure it proposes for each party. If the claimant proposes Model C Disclosure for any Issue for Disclosure it should indicate, using Section 1 B of the Disclosure Review Document, how the particular documents or narrow class of documents it proposes should be defined for that purpose (see paragraph 8 below).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_57", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.3", "subsection_index": 57, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.4 If the claimant fails to prepare and serve a List of Issues for Disclosure within 42 days of the final statement of case any defendant may prepare and serve its own draft List of Issues for Disclosure on the other parties together with its proposed Models including any Model C requests.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_58", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.4", "subsection_index": 58, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.5 A List of Issues for Disclosure is not required if the parties are agreed that Extended Disclosure is to be confined to Models A and B.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_59", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.5", "subsection_index": 59, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.6, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.6 The List of Issues for Disclosure should be as short and concise as possible. "Issues for Disclosure" means for the purposes of disclosure only those key issues in dispute, which the parties consider will need to be determined by the court with some reference to contemporaneous documents in order for there to be a fair resolution of the proceedings. It does not extend to every issue which is disputed in the statements of case by denial or non-admission. For the purposes of producing a List of Issues for Disclosure the parties should consider what matters are common ground but should only include the key issues in dispute in the list.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_60", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.6", "subsection_index": 60, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.7, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.7 When drafting Issues for Disclosure the parties should have regard to the primary functions of those Issues namely (i) to help the parties to consider, and the court to determine, whether Extended Disclosure is required and, if so, which Model or Models should be used; (ii) to assist the parties in identifying documents and categories of documents that are likely to exist and require to be disclosed; (iii) to assist those carrying out the disclosure process to do so in a practical and proportionate way including, in the case of search-based disclosure, to help define and guide the searches; (iv) to assist with the process of reviewing documents produced by searches; and (v) to avoid the production of documents that are not relevant to the issues in the proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_61", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.7", "subsection_index": 61, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.8, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.8 The claimant should seek to ensure that the draft List of Issues for Disclosure provides a fair and balanced summary of the key areas of dispute identified by the parties' statements of case and in respect of which it is likely that one or other of the parties will be seeking search-based Extended Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_62", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.8", "subsection_index": 62, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.9, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.9 A party served with a draft List of Issues for Disclosure and proposals on Models shall, as soon as practicable but in any event no later than 21 days from service, indicate using Section 1 A (and, if applicable, 1 B) of the Disclosure Review Document whether it agrees with the proposals (including any proposals as to how Model C Disclosure should be defined). If the party served with the proposals does not agree, or wishes to propose alternative or additional Issues for Disclosure, other Models and/or other Model C proposals, it should set out its alternative or additional proposals in Sections 1 A and 1 B of the Disclosure Review Document.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_63", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.9", "subsection_index": 63, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.10, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.10 In advance of the first case management conference, the parties must discuss and seek to agree the draft List of Issues for Disclosure, the Models identified for each Issue for Disclosure, and the wording of any Model C proposals. They should consider whether any draft Issue for Disclosure can be removed.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_64", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.10", "subsection_index": 64, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.11, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.11 Whilst reasonable and proportionate efforts are required to agree the List of Issues for Disclosure, if agreement cannot be reached after such efforts the List should be concluded by showing the areas of disagreement. The parties should consider seeking Disclosure Guidance from the court at an early stage as a means to help resolve the differences between them. One situation in which Disclosure Guidance should be considered is where one party believes the other is proposing a list of issues that is far too complex to serve as a List of Issues for Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_65", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.11", "subsection_index": 65, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.12, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.12 The List of Issues for Disclosure does not bind the parties at trial. The List of Issues for Disclosure need not contain / include a list of all the issues in the case and the issues in the case may develop or be refined as the case proceeds. The List of Issues for Disclosure may be revised or supplemented at any time prior to or following the case management conference, including as a result of statements of case or amended statements of case subsequently served or discussions between the parties in relation to the Disclosure Review Document.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_66", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.12", "subsection_index": 66, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.2, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.2 Under CPR25.1 the court has power to grant various interim remedies, and applications for these are dealt with in Section 12 below. Under CPR25.2 the court can grant interim remedies before proceedings are started, and without notice having been given to the other party, but this is subject to various conditions.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_0", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.2", "subsection_index": 0, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.3, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.3 A High Court Judge is available on every day that the court is sitting both in normal hours and out of hours to deal with applications for interim remedies. Applications should be made to the Interim Applications Judge (who normally sits in Court 37). The practice and procedure is set out in paragraphs 9.55 to 9.61 and section 11.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_1", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.3", "subsection_index": 1, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.4, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.4 Masters have jurisdiction to grant various interim remedies, other than freezing and search orders (see PD2B paragraph 2). However, all applications for interim injunctions should be made to a High Court Judge.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_2", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.4", "subsection_index": 2, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.5, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.5 Applications are required to approve interim payments in claims involving children and protected parties. Those interim payments may be made at a time when a claim would not normally be issued. In those cases, a Part 8 claim should be issued, and any further applications for interim payments made in the Part 8 claim. See section 13 below for the procedure for approval of interim payments and of settlements.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_3", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.5", "subsection_index": 3, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.6, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.6 A person intending to make a claim may need documents within the control of a likely party to a claim to which they do not yet have access. If the documents are not disclosed voluntarily, in accordance with the Pre-Action Protocols, then CPR31.16 sets out the provisions for making an application for disclosure of documents before proceedings have started. If such an application is made and a claim is later issued, the claim will have a different case number, but the court should be told about the pre-action application and the two cases will be linked on CE file.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_4", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.6", "subsection_index": 4, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.7, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.7 It may also be possible, where proceedings have not yet been started, to make an application for an order for disclosure of documents and information from other sources, who are not likely to be a party to the claim. Pursuant to Norwich Pharmacal v Customs and Excise Commissioners [1974] AC 133 HL, the court may order documents and information to be provided by persons alleged to have been caught up in the wrongs of others. These applications should be made by Part 8 claim form (unless there is a dispute of fact in which case a Part 7 claim form is likely to be appropriate). The application will be placed in the first instance before a Master and will be referred to a High Court judge if the capacity and/or importance of the application warrants it; if the applicant wishes for the application to be dealt with by a High Court Judge, consent from the Master should be sought.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_5", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.7", "subsection_index": 5, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.8, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.8 An application may be made to the court before a claim is brought for the court's assistance in accepting an offer of amends under section 3 of the Defamation Act 1996. The application is made by a Part 8 Claim Form. For more information see section 8 (Part 8 procedure) and section 17 (Media and Communications List) below.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_6", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.8", "subsection_index": 6, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.9, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.9 Permission may be required to serve proceedings or documents out of the jurisdiction. Such applications are made by way of application notice and will usually be dealt with by a Master. The application is usually dealt with on paper. See CPR6.36 to 6.38 and paragraph 6.10 below.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_7", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.9", "subsection_index": 7, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.10, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.10 The applicant must be candid and should draw to the attention of the court in the evidence in support of the application all relevant matters including those which are adverse to the application. A failure to do so may lead to the order giving permission to be struck out.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_8", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.10", "subsection_index": 8, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.11, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.11 Open justice is a fundamental principle of our court system. The general rule is that the names of the parties to a claim are included in all court documents, orders and judgments and hearings are publicly listed with the names of the parties.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_9", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.11", "subsection_index": 9, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.12, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.12 However, the Court does have powers: (a) to permit a Claim Form to be issued without a party's name or address (b) to prevent disclosure of the identity of a claimant or other person; and (c) to prevent or restrict public access to documents on the court file, including statements of case (CPR 5.4C). Such orders will not be made simply because the parties consent. Any departure from the principle of open justice should be the minimum strictly necessary in the interests of justice and for the proper administration of justice. Where the court has permitted a name or other matter to be withheld from the public, the court can impose reporting restrictions under s.ll Contempt of Court Act 1981 prohibiting the publication of that name in connection with the proceedings.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_10", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.12", "subsection_index": 10, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.13, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.13 Applications for such orders can be made on issue. Applications should usually be made to a Master. The application should be made at the same time as issuing the claim form and not before. The file will be made private until the application is dealt with. The application should usually be supported by appropriate evidence and a short skeleton argument.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_11", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.13", "subsection_index": 11, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/202