Standard disclosure - what documents are to be disclosed", "filepath": "Disclosure and Inspection of Documents", "groups": [], "id": "Part_31___Disclosure_and_Inspection_of_Documents_subsection_4", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Part_31___Disclosure_and_Inspection_of_Documents", "reranker_score": 2.61181378364563, "score": 0.02460360899567604, "sourcefile": "Part 31", "sourcepage": "Disclosure and Inspection of Documents", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part31", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part31", "subsection_id": "31.5", "subsection_index": 4, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2024-04-06T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part31"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "31.6, Disclosure and Inspection of Documents, Part 31", "content": "31.6 Standard disclosure requires a party to disclose only-

(a) the documents on which he relies; and

(b) the documents which -

(i) adversely affect his own case;

(ii) adversely affect another party's case; or

(iii) support another party's case; and

(c) the documents which he is required to disclose by a relevant practice direction.

