Duty of disclosure limited to documents which are or have been in a party's control", "filepath": "Disclosure and Inspection of Documents", "groups": [], "id": "Part_31___Disclosure_and_Inspection_of_Documents_subsection_6", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Part_31___Disclosure_and_Inspection_of_Documents", "reranker_score": 2.61181378364563, "score": 0.02460360899567604, "sourcefile": "Part 31", "sourcepage": "Disclosure and Inspection of Documents", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part31", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part31", "subsection_id": "31.7", "subsection_index": 6, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2024-04-06T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part31"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "31.8, Disclosure and Inspection of Documents, Part 31", "content": "31.8

(1) A party's duty to disclose documents is limited to documents which are or have been in his control.

(2) For this purpose a party has or has had a document in his control if -

(a) it is or was in his physical possession;

(b) he has or has had a right to possession of it; or

(c) he has or has had a right to inspect or take copies of it.

